data.description: High and Dry in Shore Acres!  This home has faired very well during our recent storms!  No flooding inside the living area, and no damage to the roof or exterior of the home.  Welcome home to this adorable newly listed home that has a lot to offer! There are many recent updates, including granite counters and new appliances in the kitchen, electric tankless water heater, a 200 Amp electrical panel and solar panels on the roof which have reduced the electric bill to only $35. per month in the heat of the summer!  The solar panels are paid off so there is no longer a lease fee!  The bathroom has also been updated with tastefully done tile in the shower and an attractive vanity.  The interior central heating and cooling are controlled by a smart "Nest" thermostat, and all of the windows are newer than original.  There is lots of natural light flowing into the living spaces, and this brightens up the original oak hardwood floors and helps to showcase the coved ceiling features.  The kitchen has a breakfast bar, and just beyond that, there is a large dining room where you can welcome your friends or family.  In the rear of the house there is a comfortable porch that has tiled flooring and is completely screened in.  The rear yard in enclosed by a vinyl fence with side gate.  There are also mature trees and shrubs throughout the yard, and some of these trees even provide seasonal  fruit! While this home is sitting high and dry, the lot has many features including a circular driveway and great private parking off street.  It's important to note just how close this house is the Shore Acres Recreation Center, and stores like the new Fresh Market, the Islander Market and Publix just down the street.  This location is very convenient to Downtown St. Petersburg, a few Public Golf courses, and our Gulf beaches.  If you're interested in boating, the Intracoastal Waterway and a Community boat ramp are close by. Don't miss out on this super clean and move in ready home in a very well located neighborhood!  Schedule your visit today.
